---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" activePage="" description="Purple Directive privacy policy — how we handle your data when you use our website and purchase our products.">

  <section class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: March 24, 2026</p>

    <p>
      Purple Directive LLC ("we", "us", "our") operates the website purpledirective.com.
      This page describes how we collect, use, and protect your information when you visit
      our site or purchase our products.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>When You Visit Our Site</h3>
    <p>
      We use Cloudflare Web Analytics, a privacy-first analytics service that does not use
      cookies, does not track individual visitors, and does not collect personal information.
      It measures aggregate page views and referral sources only.
    </p>

    <h3>When You Make a Purchase</h3>
    <p>
      Purchases are processed through Stripe, a PCI-compliant payment processor. When you
      purchase a product, Stripe collects your payment information (card number, billing
      address, email). We do not store your payment details on our servers. We receive your
      name and email address from Stripe in order to deliver your purchase.
    </p>

    <h3>When You Contact Us</h3>
    <p>
      If you email us at info@purpledirective.com or use our contact form, we receive
      your name, email address, and message content. We use this only to respond to your inquiry.
    </p>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To deliver products you purchase (email with download link)</li>
      <li>To respond to support requests or inquiries</li>
      <li>To understand aggregate site traffic (no individual tracking)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <table class="legal-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Data Shared</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Stripe</td><td>Payment processing</td><td>Payment details, email, name</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Cloudflare</td><td>Hosting, analytics, security</td><td>Aggregate traffic data (no PII)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Microsoft 365</td><td>Email delivery</td><td>Your email address (for purchase delivery)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Purchase records (name, email, transaction ID) are retained for accounting and tax
      purposes. You may request deletion of your data by emailing
      <a href="mailto:info@purpledirective.com">info@purpledirective.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Our website does not set first-party cookies. Stripe may set cookies during the
      checkout process on their domain. Cloudflare may set a security cookie
      (<code>__cf_bm</code>) to distinguish humans from bots.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
      All connections to purpledirective.com are encrypted via TLS (HTTPS). Payment
      processing is handled entirely by Stripe's PCI DSS Level 1 certified infrastructure.
      We do not store credit card numbers or CVVs.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Our products and services are intended for clinical research professionals.
      We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page
      with an updated "Last updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this privacy policy? Email us at
      <a href="mailto:info@purpledirective.com">info@purpledirective.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 680px;
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .legal-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-page h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-page h3 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .legal-page p,
  .legal-page li {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-page ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: var(--spacing-sm) 0;
  }

  .legal-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .legal-page a {
    color: var(--purple-primary);
  }

  .legal-page code {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    background: var(--bg-tinted);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .legal-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;
  }

  .legal-table th {
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-table td {
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
</style>
